Tabulate Fish Numbers

Source: R/tabulate.R
ypr_tabulate_fish.Rd

Produces a data frame of the number of fish in the 'Survivors', 'Spawners', 'Caught', 'Harvested', 'Released' and 'HandlingMortalities' categories by 'Length', 'Age' or 'Weight' class.

ypr_tabulate_fish(population, x = "Age", binwidth = 1L)

Arguments

population

An object of class ypr_population().

x

The object to coerce.

binwidth

A positive integer of the width of the bins for grouping.

Value

A data frame

See also

Other tabulate: ypr_detabulate_parameters(), ypr_report(), ypr_tabulate_biomass(), ypr_tabulate_parameters(), ypr_tabulate_schedule(), ypr_tabulate_sr(), ypr_tabulate_yields(), ypr_tabulate_yield()

Other fish: ypr_plot_fish()

Examples

ypr_tabulate_fish(ypr_population())
